tables.name: CUSTOMERS
tables.desc: Details of the people placing orders

columns.name: CUSTOMER_ID
columns.desc: Auto-incrementing primary key

columns.name: EMAIL_ADDRESS
columns.desc: The email address the person uses to access the account

columns.name: FULL_NAME
columns.desc: What this customer is called

tables.name: ORDERS
tables.desc: Details of who made purchases where

columns.name: CUSTOMER_ID
columns.desc: Who placed this order

columns.name: ORDER_DATETIME
columns.desc: When the order was placed

columns.name: ORDER_ID
columns.desc: Auto-incrementing primary key

columns.name: ORDER_STATUS
columns.desc: What state the order is in. Valid values are: OPEN - the order is in progress PAID - money has been received from the customer for this order SHIPPED - the products have been dispatched to the customer COMPLETE - the customer has received the order CANCELLED - the customer has stopped the order REFUNDED - there has been an issue with the order and the money has been returned to the customer

columns.name: STORE_ID
columns.desc: Where this order was placed

tables.name: ORDER_ITEMS
tables.desc: Details of which products the customer has purchased in an order

columns.name: LINE_ITEM_ID
columns.desc: An incrementing number, starting at one for each order

columns.name: ORDER_ID
columns.desc: The order these products belong to

columns.name: PRODUCT_ID
columns.desc: Which item was purchased

columns.name: QUANTITY
columns.desc: How many items of this product the customer purchased

columns.name: UNIT_PRICE
columns.desc: How much the customer paid for one item of the product

tables.name: PRODUCTS
tables.desc: Details of goods that customers can purchase

columns.name: IMAGE_CHARSET
columns.desc: The character set used to encode the image

columns.name: IMAGE_FILENAME
columns.desc: The name of the file loaded in the image column

columns.name: IMAGE_LAST_UPDATED
columns.desc: The date the image was last changed

columns.name: IMAGE_MIME_TYPE
columns.desc: The mime-type of the product image

columns.name: PRODUCT_DETAILS
columns.desc: Further details of the product stored in JSON format

columns.name: PRODUCT_ID
columns.desc: Auto-incrementing primary key

columns.name: PRODUCT_IMAGE
columns.desc: A picture of the product

columns.name: PRODUCT_NAME
columns.desc: What a product is called

columns.name: UNIT_PRICE
columns.desc: The monetary value of one item of this product

tables.name: STORES
tables.desc: Physical and virtual locations where people can purchase products

columns.name: LATITUDE
columns.desc: The north-south position of a physical store

columns.name: LOGO
columns.desc: An image used by this store

columns.name: LOGO_CHARSET
columns.desc: The character set used to encode the image

columns.name: LOGO_FILENAME
columns.desc: The name of the file loaded in the image column

columns.name: LOGO_LAST_UPDATED
columns.desc: The date the image was last changed

columns.name: LOGO_MIME_TYPE
columns.desc: The mime-type of the store logo

columns.name: LONGITUDE
columns.desc: The east-west position of a physical store

columns.name: PHYSICAL_ADDRESS
columns.desc: The postal address of this location

columns.name: STORE_ID
columns.desc: Auto-incrementing primary key

columns.name: STORE_NAME
columns.desc: What the store is called

columns.name: WEB_ADDRESS
columns.desc: The URL of a virtual store

tables.name: COUNTRIES
tables.desc: country table. Contains 25 rows. References with locations table.

columns.name: COUNTRY_ID
columns.desc: Primary key of countries table.

columns.name: COUNTRY_NAME
columns.desc: Country name

columns.name: REGION_ID
columns.desc: Region ID for the country. Foreign key to region_id column in the departments table.

tables.name: DEPARTMENTS
tables.desc: Departments table that shows details of departments where employees work. Contains 27 rows; references with locations, employees, and job_history tables.

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.desc: Primary key column of departments table.

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_NAME
columns.desc: A not null column that shows name of a department. Administration, Marketing, Purchasing, Human Resources, Shipping, IT, Executive, Public Relations, Sales, Finance, and Accounting.

columns.name: LOCATION_ID
columns.desc: Location id where a department is located. Foreign key to location_id column of locations table.

columns.name: MANAGER_ID
columns.desc: Manager_id of a department. Foreign key to employee_id column of employees table. The manager_id column of the employee table references this column.

tables.name: EMPLOYEES
tables.desc: employees table. Contains 107 rows. References with departments, jobs, job_history tables. Contains a self reference.

columns.name: COMMISSION_PCT
columns.desc: Commission percentage of the employee; Only employees in sales department elgible for commission percentage

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.desc: Department id where employee works; foreign key to department_id column of the departments table

columns.name: EMAIL
columns.desc: Email id of the employee

columns.name: EMPLOYEE_ID
columns.desc: Primary key of employees table.

columns.name: FIRST_NAME
columns.desc: First name of the employee. A not null column.

columns.name: HIRE_DATE
columns.desc: Date when the employee started on this job. A not null column.

columns.name: JOB_ID
columns.desc: Current job of the employee; foreign key to job_id column of the jobs table. A not null column.

columns.name: LAST_NAME
columns.desc: Last name of the employee. A not null column.

columns.name: MANAGER_ID
columns.desc: Manager id of the employee; has same domain as manager_id in departments table. Foreign key to employee_id column of employees table. (useful for reflexive joins and CONNECT BY query)

columns.name: PHONE_NUMBER
columns.desc: Phone number of the employee; includes country code and area code

columns.name: SALARY
columns.desc: Monthly salary of the employee. Must be greater than zero (enforced by constraint emp_salary_min)

tables.name: JOBS
tables.desc: jobs table with job titles and salary ranges. Contains 19 rows. References with employees and job_history table.

columns.name: JOB_ID
columns.desc: Primary key of jobs table.

columns.name: JOB_TITLE
columns.desc: A not null column that shows job title, e.g. AD_VP, FI_ACCOUNTANT

columns.name: MAX_SALARY
columns.desc: Maximum salary for a job title

columns.name: MIN_SALARY
columns.desc: Minimum salary for a job title.

tables.name: JOB_HISTORY
tables.desc: Table that stores job history of the employees. If an employee changes departments within the job or changes jobs within the department, new rows get inserted into this table with old job information of the employee. Contains a complex primary key: employee_id+start_date. Contains 25 rows. References with jobs, employees, and departments tables.

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.desc: Department id in which the employee worked in the past; foreign key to deparment_id column in the departments table

columns.name: EMPLOYEE_ID
columns.desc: A not null column in the complex primary key employee_id+start_date. Foreign key to employee_id column of the employee table

columns.name: END_DATE
columns.desc: Last day of the employee in this job role. A not null column. Must be greater than the start_date of the job_history table. (enforced by constraint jhist_date_interval)

columns.name: JOB_ID
columns.desc: Job role in which the employee worked in the past; foreign key to job_id column in the jobs table. A not null column.

columns.name: START_DATE
columns.desc: A not null column in the complex primary key employee_id+start_date. Must be less than the end_date of the job_history table. (enforced by constraint jhist_date_interval)

tables.name: LOCATIONS
tables.desc: Locations table that contains specific address of a specific office, warehouse, and/or production site of a company. Does not store addresses / locations of customers. Contains 23 rows; references with the departments and countries tables.

columns.name: CITY
columns.desc: A not null column that shows city where an office, warehouse, or production site of a company is located.

columns.name: COUNTRY_ID
columns.desc: Country where an office, warehouse, or production site of a company is located. Foreign key to country_id column of the countries table.

columns.name: LOCATION_ID
columns.desc: Primary key of locations table

columns.name: POSTAL_CODE
columns.desc: Postal code of the location of an office, warehouse, or production site of a company.

columns.name: STATE_PROVINCE
columns.desc: State or Province where an office, warehouse, or production site of a company is located.

columns.name: STREET_ADDRESS
columns.desc: Street address of an office, warehouse, or production site of a company. Contains building number and street name
